      <abstract>
        <p><italic>Campylobacter coli </italic>is a rare cause of bacteremia. We report here the first case of <italic>C.coli </italic>spondylodiscitis complicated by an aortic aneurysm. Outcome was favourable with surgery and antibiotic therapy.</p>
      </abstract>
    </article-meta>
